      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Major] Line 316: The normal-priority early return happens after activePushCount.incrementAndGet(), but JamiApplication does not balance that increment itself. This makes correctness depend on every caller knowing it must call onPushProcessed() after a lightweight push; any future or existing non-Firebase caller using onPushReceived(false) will leak activePushCount and may keep shutdown state incorrect. Prefer keeping the accounting balanced inside this method, or return a status that forces callers to handle it explicitly. For example:\n```suggestion\n        if (!isHighPriority \u0026\u0026 !isInForeground) {\n            Log.d(TAG, \"Push: normal priority in background, lightweight handling\")\n            activePushCount.decrementAndGet()\n            return\n        }\n```",
